nalized—the urban poor, transvestite and female prostitutes, discapacitados (the physically challenged), gays and lesbians, and artists and intellectuals. Blending portraits of and comments by group members with their own ethnographic observations, the authors reveal how such issues as racism, sexism, sexuality, spirituality, and class struggle play out in the people's daily lives and in grassroots political activism. By doing so, they translate the abstract concepts of social action and identity formation into the actual lived experiences of real people.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aArtistszMexicozOaxaca de Juárez. 0aCultural pluralismzMexicozOaxaca de Juárez. 0aGays -- Mexico -- Oaxaca de Juárez. 0aGayszMexicozOaxaca de Juárez. 0aGayszMexicozOaxaca de Juárez. 0aIntellectualszMexicozOaxaca de Juárez. 0aLesbianszMexicozOaxaca de Juárez. 0aOaxaca de Juárez (Mexico) -- Social conditions. 0aPeople with disabilitieszMexicozOaxaca de Juárez. 0aPoor -- Mexico -- Oaxaca de Juárez. 0aPoorzMexicozOaxaca de Juárez. 0aPoorzMexicozOaxaca de Juárez. 0aSex workerszMexicozOaxaca de Juárez. 0aSocial groups -- Mexico -- Oaxaca de Juárez. 0aSocial groupszMexicozOaxaca de Juárez. 0aSocial groupszMexicozOaxaca de Juárez. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aCoen, Tanya L., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/73133240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292731790423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292731790/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK